<h1 style="text-align:center"><strong>Order of Mass</strong><br />
<span style="font-size:13px">Penned by Cardinal Marius Neminelah</span></h1>

<hr />
<h3 style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:22px"><u><strong>Introductary Rites</strong></u></span></h3>

<h3 style="text-align:center"><br />
~</h3>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:18px"><strong>Entrance Procession</strong></span></p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:undefined"><em>After the people have assembled, a Gathering Song or Entrance Antiphon is sung or recited as the priest and the ministers enter the church and process to the altar; after reverencing the altar, and sometimes also using incense, they go to their chairs.</em></span></p>

<p style="text-align:center">~</p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:18px"><strong>Liturgical Greeting</strong></span></p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:undefined"><em>All together make the sign of the Aquila.</em></span></p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:undefined"><span style="font-size:14px"><strong>Confessor:</strong></span> In the name of the God-Emperor who sits on the Golden Throne.</span></p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:undefined"><strong><span style="font-size:14px">All:</span> </strong>The Emperor Protects</span></p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:undefined"><span style="font-size:14px"><strong>Confessor: </strong>God-Emperor be with you</span></span></p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:undefined"><strong><span style="font-size:14px">All:</span> </strong>And with thy spirit.</span></p>

<p style="text-align:center">~</p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:18px"><strong>Penitential Act</strong></span></p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:undefined"><span style="font-size:14px"><strong>Confessor:</strong></span> Brothers and sisters, let us acknowledge our sins, and so prepare ourselves to celebrate the sacred mysteries</span></p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:undefined"><span style="font-size:14px"><strong>Confessor:</strong></span> Have mercy on us, O God-Emperor.</span></p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:undefined"><strong><span style="font-size:14px">All:</span> </strong>For we have sinned against you</span></p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:undefined"><span style="font-size:14px"><strong>Confessor:</strong></span> Show us, O Emperor, your mercy.</span></p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:undefined"><strong><span style="font-size:14px">All:</span> </strong>and grant us your salvation.</span></p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:undefined"><span style="font-size:14px"><strong>Confessor:</strong></span> </span>May the Immortal Emperor have mercy on us, and bring us to everlasting life.</p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:undefined"><strong><span style="font-size:14px">All: </span></strong><span style="font-size:14px">the Emperor protects.</span></span></p>

<p style="text-align:center">~</p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:18px"><strong>Kyrie</strong></span></p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:undefined"><span style="font-size:14px"><strong>Confessor:</strong></span> </span>God-Emperor have mercy.</p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:undefined"><strong><span style="font-size:14px">All:</span> </strong>God-Emperor have mercy.</span></p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:undefined"><span style="font-size:14px"><strong>Confessor:</strong></span> </span>Immortal Emperor protect us from the alien.</p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:undefined"><strong><span style="font-size:14px">All:</span> </strong>God-Emperor have mercy.</span></p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:undefined"><span style="font-size:14px"><strong>Confessor:</strong></span> </span>Master of the Universe protect us from the heretic.</p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:undefined"><strong><span style="font-size:14px">All:</span> </strong>God-Emperor have mercy.</span></p>

<p style="text-align:center">~</p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:18px"><strong>Adulation</strong></span></p>

<p style="text-align:center"><strong>All:</strong></p>

<p style="text-align:center">Adore the Immortal Emperor for He is our protector.</p>

<p style="text-align:center">Admire the Immortal Emperor for His sacrifice to mankind.</p>

<p style="text-align:center">Exalt the Immortal Emperor for His strict guidance.</p>

<p style="text-align:center">Revere the Immortal Emperor for His undying guard.</p>

<p style="text-align:center">Venerate the Immortal Emperor for His holy wisdom.</p>

<p style="text-align:center">Honor the Immortal Emperor for His eternal strength.</p>

<p style="text-align:center">Glorify the Immortal Emperor for His all-seeing vision.</p>

<p style="text-align:center">Praise the Immortal Emperor for his unending rule.</p>

<p style="text-align:center">Hail the Immortal Emperor for He is our Lord and Master.</p>

<p style="text-align:center">Worship the Immortal Emperor for without Him we are nothing.</p>

<p style="text-align:center">~</p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:18px"><strong>Collect</strong></span></p>

<p style="text-align:center">~</p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:undefined"><span style="font-size:14px"><strong>Confessor:</strong></span> </span>Let us pray.</p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:undefined"><em>After a time of silent prayer, the priest sings or says the Collect, which is different for each Mass. At the end, the people proclaim their consent.</em></span></p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:undefined"><strong><span style="font-size:14px">All:</span> </strong>The Emperor Protects</span></p>

<p style="text-align:center">~</p>

<hr />
<p style="text-align:center"><br />
<span style="font-size:22px"><u><strong>Liturgy of the Word</strong></u></span></p>

<p style="text-align:center">~</p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:18px"><strong>Reading</strong></span></p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:undefined"><span style="font-size:14px"><strong>Confessor:</strong></span></span> A reading from the Book of... <em>or</em> the Letter of...; <em>or</em> the Acts of the Saints.</p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:undefined"><em>Different readings are prescribed for each day.</em><br />
<em>At the end of the reading, the lector proclaims, and the people respond:</em></span></p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:undefined"><span style="font-size:14px"><strong>Confessor: </strong>the word of the Lord.</span></span></p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:undefined"><strong><span style="font-size:14px">All:</span> </strong>Thanks be to the God-Emperor.</span></p>

<p style="text-align:center">~</p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:18px"><strong>Homily</strong></span></p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:undefined"><em>The confessor, priest, or deacon then speaks to the people, usually focusing on that day&#39;s scriptures and/or on the feast or special occasion being celebrated at that Mass; the homily may also be based on any liturgical text from the Mass.</em></span></p>

<p style="text-align:center">~</p>

<p style="text-align:center"><strong><span style="font-size:18px">Profession of Faith</span></strong></p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:undefined"><span style="font-size:14px"><strong>Confessor: Let us pray</strong></span></span></p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:undefined"><strong><span style="font-size:14px">All: </span></strong><em><span style="font-size:14px">stand</span></em><strong> </strong></span></p>

<p style="text-align:center">I believe in the one God, the Emperor of Man.</p>

<p style="text-align:center">Who watched us and guided us before all ages.</p>

<p style="text-align:center">For our sake he was immolated,</p>

<p style="text-align:center">he suffered and was inturred upon the Golden Throne,</p>

<p style="text-align:center">and though he is sundered he watches and protects us all.</p>

<p style="text-align:center">He will come again and His kingdom will have no end.</p>

<p style="text-align:center"><br />
<br />
I believe in His word,</p>

<p style="text-align:center">his truth that is adored and glorified,</p>

<p style="text-align:center">that is spoken through prophets.</p>

<p style="text-align:center">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="text-align:center">I believe in one Holy Ecclesiarchy,</p>

<p style="text-align:center">the communion of Saints,</p>

<p style="text-align:center">the forgiveness of sins,</p>

<p style="text-align:center">the resurrection of the body,</p>

<p style="text-align:center">and life everlasting.</p>

<p style="text-align:center">~</p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:18px"><strong>Prayer of the faithful</strong></span></p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:undefined"><span style="font-size:14px"><strong>Confessor: </strong>Let us pray</span></span></p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:undefined"><span style="font-size:14px"><strong>Confessor: </strong></span></span>Love the God-Emperor,</p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:undefined"><strong><span style="font-size:14px">All: </span></strong></span>For He is the salvation of mankind.</p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:undefined"><span style="font-size:14px"><strong>Confessor: </strong>Obey His word,</span></span></p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:undefined"><strong><span style="font-size:14px">All:</span></strong></span> For He will lead you into the light of the future.</p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:undefined"><span style="font-size:14px"><strong>Confessor: </strong>Heed his wisdom,</span></span></p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:undefined"><strong><span style="font-size:14px">All: </span></strong>For it will protect you from evils.</span></p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:undefined"><span style="font-size:14px"><strong>Confessor: </strong></span></span>Honour His Servants</p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:undefined"><strong><span style="font-size:14px">All: </span></strong>For they speak in His voice</span></p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:undefined"><span style="font-size:14px"><strong>Confessor: </strong>Tremble before His majesty</span></span></p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:undefined"><strong><span style="font-size:14px">All: </span></strong>for we all walk in His immortal shadow.</span><br />
<br />
~</p>

<hr />
<p style="text-align:center"><br />
&nbsp;</p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:22px"><u><strong>Liturgy of the Sacrament</strong></u></span></p>

<p style="text-align:center"><br />
~</p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:18px"><strong>Presentation of Gifts</strong></span></p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:undefined"><span style="font-size:14px"><strong>Confessor: </strong></span></span>Blessed are you, Lord God of all humanity,</p>

<p style="text-align:center">for through your goodness we have received the bread we offer you:</p>

<p style="text-align:center">fruit of the earth and work of human hands, it will become for us the bread of life.</p>

<p style="text-align:center"><em>bread is brought to the altar as a sacrament</em></p>

<p style="text-align:center">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:undefined"><strong><span style="font-size:14px">All:</span></strong></span> Praise the God-Emperor now and forever.</p>

<p style="text-align:center">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:undefined"><span style="font-size:14px"><strong>Confessor: </strong></span></span>Blessed are you, Lord God of all humanity,</p>

<p style="text-align:center">for through your goodness we have received the wine we offer you:</p>

<p style="text-align:center">fruit of the vine and work of human hands it will become our spiritual drink.</p>

<p style="text-align:center"><em>wine is brought to the altar as a sacrament</em></p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:undefined"><strong><span style="font-size:14px">All:</span></strong></span> Praise the God-Emperor now and forever.</p>

<p style="text-align:center">~</p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:undefined"><span style="font-size:14px"><strong>Confessor: </strong>Pray, brothers and sisters, that my sacrifices and yours may be acceptable to the God-Emperor</span></span></p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:undefined"><em>The confessor sings or says this prayer, which is different for each Mass. At the end, the people sing or say in response:</em></span></p>

<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:undefined"><strong><span style="font-size:14px">All:</span></strong></span> The Emperor protects.<br />
